{"key":"processedPost-10832490","value":{"id":10832490,"first":10827734,"last":10832930,"when":1249924147,"utime":"08/10/09 08:09 PM","content":"The shotgun terrarium as designed will be fine for FAE and humidity for the three days you're gone.&nbsp; Don't even attempt to automate misting though.&nbsp; That requires visually inspecting the substrates and then misting as required.&nbsp; It's important that the substrate begins to dry out, and then you replace that moisture.&nbsp; If it waterlogs or stays in a constant state, fruiting performance will be nil or poor.<br /><br />If you leave for three days, mist will before you leave, and if the substrates are dry when you return, soak them in water to rehydrate.<br />RR","title":"Re: Automated fae and mist on shotgun fc Idea?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}